---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Resources">
  <div class="page-head">
    <span class="eyebrow">Resources</span>
    <h1>The free library</h1>
    <p class="standfirst">
      Everything Econschool makes that you can use right now, at no cost.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>The YouTube channel</h2>
  <p>
    Full lectures and problem-solving videos in microeconomics and mathematics —
    including the <strong>research-to-problem</strong> series, where results from
    major papers (Akerlof, Milgrom, Diamond–Dybvig, and others) are restated as
    problems solvable with MA-level tools and worked in full.
  </p>
  <p><a class="button secondary" href="https://www.youtube.com/@econ.school">Open the channel</a></p>

  <h2>The Econ Artbook</h2>
  <p>
    A hundred-page collection of mathematical postcards — one concept per card,
    drawn in TikZ and Mathcha with the same color conventions used across this
    site. Made to be studied slowly, one card at a time.
  </p>
  <!-- NOTE FOR AMIT: add the Artbook link or download here. -->

  <h2>Companion PDFs</h2>
  <p>
    Each research-to-problem video has a one- to two-page companion PDF: problem
    statement, full solution, and extension exercises. They are linked from the
    corresponding entries in <a href="/problems/">Problems &amp; Tools</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>The community forum</h2>
  <p>
    Doubts, attempted solutions, and discussion live in the community forum, where
    a question asked once helps everyone who comes after. Details for joining are
    shared with program and workshop participants, and on the
    <a href="/announcements/">announcements page</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>
